# 2. それぞれの目指すもの

Rin: Hey, girls! What's up☆
Honami: Hello, Rin.
Saki: Oh, you guys gotta hear this! Today, we went over to the record company to talk with Mr. Shindo!
Luka: With Mr. Shindo? What did you all discuss?
MEIKO: We'd love to hear all about it.
Ichika: Okay. So, it started with a discussion surrounding how we'll be marketed for our debut...
Rin: What you want your music to be about...?
Shiho: Yeah. We were told the company needs to know that in order to come up with a marketing strategy for Leo/need.
Len: I see... I definitely understand their reasoning.
Miku: But that's kind of a tough question to ask yourselves after coming this far...
Shiho: It is...
Shiho: I couldn't come up with even a half-decent response when Mr. Shindo asked me.
Honami: Me neither... I didn't feel comfortable saying anything in that moment...
Ichika: Shiho, Honami...
Shiho: Sorry for causing you two so much trouble.
Ichika: No, um... I just happened to get a chance to think about that not too long ago is all.
Saki: Yeah, same! Plus, Mr. Shindo said you should take your time to think it through. There's no need to rush at all!
Shiho: Thanks, Saki.
Shiho: I'll try giving it some thought when I get home.
Honami: Me too... It may take me some time, but I promise to come up with a satisfactory answer for when we next meet with Mr. Shindo.
Saki: Okay! We'll be looking forward to what you come up with!
Ichika: But if either of you get stuck, we'll be more than happy to listen or talk.
Rin: Oh, I wanna help too! I'll do whatever I can to get you through this!
Honami: Thank you all very much.
Miku: So, what else did you talk about today?
Saki: Oh, so... About the other things we need to do before we debut...
Shizuku: Shii, the bath's ready.
Shiho: You can go first. I'm sure you're all sweaty after practice.
Shizuku: Are you sure? Then, if you insist.
Shiho: *Nod*
Shindo: What aspirations do you hold for your music...?
Shiho: (My aspirations for my music, huh...?)
Shiho: (I get what Ichika and Saki want to do. Because that time...)
Honami: It's like Saki's trying to cheer us up.
Ichika: Yeah, I can almost hear her voice...
Ichika: Like she's saying, “You're not alone. We're right here.”
Shiho: (Getting to be there for the Yoshizakis and support people through our music was pretty great.)
Shiho: (But if someone were to ask if doing more of that is my top goal... Then, no, not really...)
Shiho: (I mean, the reason I started playing the bass is because...)
Shiho: Their music has a way of really getting my heart going...
Shiho: It makes me want to shout out or cry... I just can't sit still after listening to them...
Ichika: Wow...
Shiho: And I want to touch someone's heart with my music, like they did with mine.
Shiho: That's why I have to get better... I want to become a pro and reach more people.
Shiho: So that my music can really get them going too...
Shiho: (That feeling's never changed... The music I heard that day... I still remember everything they played note for note.)
Shiho: (Which is why... Being asked to come up with another goal is so...)
Shiho: (All this thinking is making me tired.)
Shiho: (I should do something else. Maybe watch a video or something and...)
Shiho: Oh, wait... They released their new song?
Shiho: Wow. I didn't realize.
Shiho: (They're as good as ever...)
Shiho: (My heart's dancing the way it always does when I listen to them. I can feel all this excitement welling up inside, and now I wanna play something...)
Rin: <Shih!>
Shiho: Rin...?
Shiho: What brings you here so late?
Rin: <So, I was wondering how you were doing after we talked earlier! I know you said you wanted to think this over on your own, but I couldn't wait around.>
Rin: <Oh, I'm really sorry if I'm interrupting!>
Shiho: That's okay. I was actually just starting to feel tired after thinking so hard.
Rin: <Okay. What a relief☆>
Rin: <Wait, huh? Were you watching a video just now?>
Shiho: Yeah, the band I like just uploaded the music video for their new song.
Rin: Oh, we got to hear a couple of their songs before! This is the band you really look up to, right, Shih?
Shiho: Yeah. I decided to start playing the bass because their show had such a huge effect on me. They're why I want to move people's hearts through the music we play.
Rin: <I see...>
Rin: <Hey, Shih! I wanna hear all about what happened back then☆>
Shiho: Huh?
Rin: <They're the reason you started playing the bass, right?>
Rin: <So, maybe what you felt in the past will help you find the answer you need for your music's future!>
Shiho: Yeah, you might be right...
Rin: <Genius, right?! Plus, I really wanna know more about what you were like when you were little!>
Shiho: What does that have to do with anything?
Shiho: Anyway, where should I start...?
Shiho: My dad's a professional musician. When I was little, he took me around to see all sorts of shows being put on by different bands...
Shiho: Then one time, I got to see that band.
